{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0d520acf-e2ab-4271-a5a8-08fce7ea8d9a","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/inconclusive in test results and display your reason message in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"df8a52ce-83b4-4c18-8085-afd239b0e0ac","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax for skipping tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to invoke tools.","outputTokens":223,"requestId":"BD00:E210B:1F581C7:2303866:6A07C4EB"},"id":"352d225b-b3f0-46d8-b65c-2f618dec5c80","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:14:24.379Z","parentId":"42d14338-010a-44a9-84c7-493b85ad7fa2"}
